<br>
Something I feel very strongly about.<br>
<br>
I *LOVE* this server.  I love the people on it. I love a lot of the characters here.  I love that I find RP ANYWHERE I go.<br>
<br>
I know that I sport an unpopular bend to a semipopular opinion, but, I feel pretty damn strongly about this server.<br>
<br>
I think the people who're upset by the fact that they no longer get hand held through their RP, makes me sad, and went a long long way towards my ending Sar's life. <br>
<br>
I saw a lot of &quot;The game won't foce you to RP the way I like, so I just won't RPwith you&quot;. <br>
<br>
And that's by people whining that RP is dead.  I got more quality, fun, interesting RP from people who the fascists say arent/can't be RPers, due to race/level/guildtags.<br>
<br>
See, I enjoy my RP.  But that's because my RP NEVER had anything to do with whether my shouts were zonewide(and, Shin and I have had some great shouting matches, SINCE the change, that we couldnt  have had before it), or whether I could group with a high elf or not.<br>
<br>
I'd have been the same Sar if the rules hadn't changed, but playing the class/race/deity combo I did, I'd have likely rerolled a lot sooner than I did, due to the insular way the evil community acts, as a whole.<br>
<br>
So, in closing, yes, a big reason I rerolled Sar was because I got tired of the &quot;There's no RP.  There's only subpar d00ds pretending to RP.  They're not blue, so they don't count as RPers...Oh, but not *you*, Sar. We don't mean *you*&quot;<br>
<br>
I called bullshit, and started playing a character that the evil community leaves alone because of both her race and her guildtags.<br>
<br>
That way, I get to RP *my* character, the way *i* want, without having to explain myself, ic or out to any of you.<br>
<br>
And one more thing.  Those who know me. Think about how it sounds for you all to go off about &quot;evils grouping with pales&quot; &quot;pales trying to play evil&quot; and all of that shit, knowing damn well that you have RPed with Sar, and *looked the other way* at Sar's relationships ooc, so your character didn't have to deal with them IC. <br>
<br>
~Trae, the disillusioned.<br>
